Careers






 



Why Denver Investments
As an independent, employee-owned investment management firm, Denver Investments is singularly focused on the investment success of its clients. But as focused as we are on our clients, we are equally committed to our people–the firm’s most valuable asset. We offer our professionals opportunities to work and grow in a collaborative culture that values each individual’s insights and expertise. A culture that is also entrepreneurial, as with a small company, but which offers the resources of a large firm. A place where dedicated professionals are driven to be the best at what they do, in order to help our clients achieve their goals. If this sounds like you, we invite you to apply for a position with our firm.
Denver Investments is an equal opportunity employer.
 
Key Accounts, Intermediary Distribution

We are seeking an experienced sales professional to manage our Key Accounts for the firm’s intermediary distribution channels, which include bank trust, TAMP (turnkey asset management program), broker/dealer, RIA, and self-directed platforms.
View Details
 
 
Consultant Relations/Institutional Sales

We are seeking an experienced institutional sales professional to pursue new business development opportunities with institutional consultants and investors including public funds, corporates (DB, DC), endowments and foundations, and insurance firms.
View Details
 
 
Internal Sales Consultant

Directly support the firm’s intermediary sales and service effort. Proactively sell investment products (both mutual funds and SMA (separately managed accounts) via phone and email through one or more of the following intermediaries: RIAs, financial advisors/brokers, banks, and TAMPs (turnkey asset management programs).
View Details
 
 
Research Analyst

Assists the Value Research Team in conducting investigative research, analysis, and portfolio construction, primarily in the Small and Mid-Cap universe, with a sole focus on dividend-paying stocks.
View Details
 
 
 



