Culture
As an independent, employee-owned investment management firm, Denver Investments is singularly focused on the investment success of its clients. But as focused as we are on our clients, we are equally committed to our people – the firm’s most valuable asset. We offer our diverse professionals opportunities to work and grow in a collaborative culture that values each individual’s insights and expertise. A culture that is also entrepreneurial, as with a small company, but which offers the resources of a large firm. A place where dedicated professionals are driven to be the best at what they do, in order to make a difference in our clients’ lives by helping them achieve their goals.
We are also dedicated to making a difference in people’s lives by giving back to the communities in which we work and live. The firm and its professionals strive to positively impact our communities in many ways including financial support, volunteering, and partnering with non-profit organizations.
 
 














 
 
 



History
Founded in 1958, Denver Investments has a long history managing equity, fixed income and balanced portfolios for a broad array of clients. Over the years, our seasoned investment professionals have navigated diverse market conditions while developing deep expertise in the investment disciplines they manage. Our professionals have gained an in-depth understanding of clients’ unique needs and the firm has expanded its investment offering based on these needs. Our commitment to our clients has been unwavering since the firm’s inception; we are in business to serve our clients as a fiduciary, by offering them the products and solutions they need to achieve their financial goals.
 
 
 
 






Inception of Firm
Founded as part of First National Bank of Denver, began managing Mid-Cap Growth equity portfolios


 



Introduction of Large-Cap Growth Equity
To expand its growth equity offering, the firm introduces a Large-Cap Growth style of investing.


 



Expansion of Fixed Income Offering
In response to client needs, the firm broadens its fixed income offering to include Intermediate and Long-Term bond portfolios.


 



Westcore Funds Formed
The Westcore family of mutual funds forms.


 



Introduction of Value Investing
The firm diversifies into Value investing strategies with the introduction of the Modern Value product, which evolved into what is now the Global Large-Cap Rising Dividend strategy.


 



Independently-Owned Firm
Investment professionals from Denver Investment Advisors, Inc. complete the purchase of the firm from the bank, resulting in a new entity and changing the ownership structure to a 100% employee-owned firm.


 



Expansion of International Small-Cap Capabilities
The firm acquires Bee & Associates, a boutique firm specializing in the management of international small-cap equities.


 



Broadening of Wealth Management Offering
The firm acquires Tempest Investment Counselors, Inc., a local money management firm specializing in managing assets for high-net-worth individuals.


 



Introduction of Micro-Cap Investing
The firm introduces a quantitatively-managed Micro-Cap strategy, leveraging over twenty years of quantitative experience at the firm.


 



Launch of Workplace Equality IndexTM
The firm launches the Workplace Equality IndexTM and related investment strategies.


 
 
 
 



